  "title": "Vet",
  "description": "<p>🐾<strong> We’re Hiring: Veterinarian (DVM)</strong><br>\n<em>Employment Type:</em> Part / Full-Time</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>About Us</strong><br>\nOmniVet is a progressive veterinary clinic committed to providing exceptional care for pets and excellent service for their owners. We pride ourselves on a collaborative, supportive team culture and are looking for a <strong>Veterinarian (DVM)</strong> to join our growing practice.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Position Overview</strong><br>\nAs a Veterinarian, you will be responsible for diagnosing, treating, and preventing illnesses in animals, while building strong, trusting relationships with clients. You’ll work closely with our team of nurses, technicians, and receptionists to ensure each patient receives the highest standard of care.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform physical examinations, diagnostics, and treatments for a variety of companion animals</li>\n  <li>Conduct surgical and dental procedures</li>\n  <li>Develop and communicate treatment plans with pet owners</li>\n  <li>Prescribe medications and provide follow-up care instructions</li>\n  <li>Supervise and mentor veterinary nurses and technicians</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate and detailed medical records</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with clinic protocols, safety, and hygiene standards</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Doctor of Veterinary Medicine (DVM)</strong> or equivalent, with valid license to practice</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years’ experience in a veterinary clinical setting preferred (new graduates will be considered)</li>\n  <li>Strong diagnostic, surgical, and communication skills</li>\n  <li>Ability to work well within a team and under pressure</li>\n  <li>Compassion, patience, and attention to detail</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Competitive salary and benefits package</li>\n  <li>Opportunities for continued professional development and training</li>\n  <li>Supportive, friendly, and collaborative work environment</li>\n  <li>Staff discounts on veterinary services and products</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>How to Apply</strong><br>\nPlease send your CV and cover letter to OmniVet.hr@gmail.com with the subject line <strong>\"Application – Veterinarian\"</strong>.</p>\n<p><br>\nJoin us in making a positive impact on the lives of pets and their families. 🐶🐱</p>",
